[{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.jl","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"Documentation for PlasmaProperties.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"PlasmaProperties","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties","text":"PlasmaProperties, a simple plasma calculator module in Julia\n\nThe module contains basic functions to compute common plasma properties, such as characteristic frequencies and lengths.\n\nIt builds on Unitful, which provides a simple unit system for physical quantities.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"index.html#Module-Index","page":"Index","title":"Module Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"Modules = [PlasmaProperties]\nOrder   = [:constant, :type, :function, :macro]","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Detailed-API","page":"Index","title":"Detailed API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"Modules = [PlasmaProperties]\nOrder   = [:constant, :type, :function, :macro]","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.Plasma","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.Plasma","text":"P = Plasma()\n\nMutable type holding plasma properties like density, temperature, etc. The show() method prints a table of the properties and derived quantities.\n\nA name can be specified to quickly select the ion mass and charge.  If units are not given, the default is mi in kg, n in 1/m^3, Te in eV, B in Gauss.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.check_or_assume-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.check_or_assume","text":"checkorassume(value,units)\n\nIf value is not a Unitful quantity, assume it is in the given units.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.f_ce-Tuple{Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.f_ce","text":"f_ce(B)\nf_ce(P::Plasma)\n\nCompute the (unsigned) cyclotron frequency of electrons in MHz. If B does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in Tesla.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.f_ci-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.f_ci","text":"f_ci(mi,Z,B)\nf_ci(P::Plasma)\n\nCompute the cyclotron frequency of ions of mass mi in MHz. If B does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in Tesla.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.f_pe-Tuple{Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.f_pe","text":"f_pe(ne)\nf_pe(P::Plasma)\n\nCompute the (unsigned) plasma frequency of electrons in MHz. If ne does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in m^-3.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.f_pi-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.f_pi","text":"f_pi(mi,Z,ni)\nf_pi(P::Plasma)\n\nCompute the plasma frequency of ions of mass mi in MHz. If ni does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in m^-3.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.force_energy_units!-Tuple{Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.force_energy_units!","text":"force_energy_units!(value)\n\nIf value is in temperature units, convert it to energy units.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.rLe-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.rLe","text":"rLe(B,vperpe)\n\nCompute the electron gyro radius in m. If B does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in Tesla. If vperpe does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in m/s.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#PlasmaProperties.位_De-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Index","title":"PlasmaProperties.位_De","text":"位_De(ne,Te)\n位_De(P::Plasma)\n\nCompute the Debye length of the plasm in m. If ne does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in m^-3. If Te does not have Unitful units, it is assumed to be in eV.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
